title: For Sale/Trade:  M35 beretta 1944
postcontent:
**ww2 beretta model 1935  "m35"**
 According to Whittington's records it was included in a delivery of 65,000 Beretta M1934/35 pistols delivered to the German Army Headquarters in Italy between Aug 1944 and Feb, 1945. Those serial # were 534000/599000.- "mine has #'s in that range"
 After the 8 September 1943 armistice between Italy and the Allies, the Germans saddled Beretta with three engineers from Germany. Moreover the factory was GARRISONED BY THE SS! Weapons of that time, even the ones produced for the Germans, bore the punch mark 4UT, (Quarto Ufficio tecnico di Controllo Armi e Munizioni--4th Technnical Control Unit...
-an C. Still, in Axis Pistols, page 107, states,
"It is likely that almost all of the 4/UT, ...were used by the German Army". He also includes two other variations in this statement, "1944 dated and blank slide Model 1935".
Ugo Menchini, in Pietro Beretta Le Automatiche, regarding an M1934, page 255, states,
"In late 1940 there appears an oval including the punch mark IVU. It refers to the 4th technical Control Unit of the FAG, where inspection was carried out."
 Note that, while they seem to represent the same inspectors, the "IVU" is not the same mark as the "4UT". The IVU would be found on the pre RSI model M1934, and the 4UT would be found on the RSI model M1935.
 These are the reasons why I believe that it is likely that all of the 4UT Berettas WERE RSI pistols!! the IVU and the 4UT were the same office, but under Italian management -the IVU, before the surrender of Italy, and German the 4UT, so after september, 8 1943.

 Near mint unissued condition, mint crown & mirror bore with hardly any wear on the internals, no rust or rust pitting. parkerized late war model, ' made when 'the jig was up' with tooling and machinery marks throughout. one extra period magazine very unique & presentable for the ww2 weapons collector!   FTF PERMIT OR VALID STATE IDENTIFICATION REQUIRED. WILL SHIP TO YOUR FFL FROM MINE. CASH LOCAL OR MONEY ORDER IF OUT OF STATE. CALL REDACTED $575 obo

title: For Sale:  NIB Colt Delta Match 10 - Limited edition 1/400
postcontent:
Offered for sale is a pristine NIB Colt Match Ten (Colt Delta Match 10) 10mm 1911. This is a limited edition run of 400 that produced by Colt at some point early in the 10mm production days. I believe these were made in the 1988-89 timeframe. This gun is number 391 of 400. As best as I've been able to determine by contacting other owners and reading on forums this gun was an early custom and accurized version of the Delta Elite. It came with Gold Cup frame, adjustable Millet sights, adjustable trigger, and adjustable hammer. I purchased the gun from the original owner several years ago. He said he had racked the slide a few times on one occasion, but other than that it has sat in his safe unfired. Since I purchased it I have only taken it out once a year to give it a nice wipe down before putting it back in the plastic. The gun is absolutely pristine. The box and paperwork are as you see in the pictures. I have not removed the red packaging tape to determine exactly what is underneath the manual. I've never been able to bring myself to shoot this one. I also own one other Match 10 that I've had customized by Colt. That one I will never part with.

Price reduced to $1400 local or $1450 shipped.  I would prefer a local sale if possible, but I am willing to ship.

I am not interested in trades. I've already made my purchase and now I need to sell this to pay for it. I really hate to part with it, but unfortunately I'm not made of money so if I want something else usually something has to go. This time this one loses.
